<HEADLINE> Nigeria President Begins Visit to Cuba </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria President Oulsegun
Obasanjo arrived here Monday on an official visit to Havana at the
invitation of Cuban leader Fidel Castro.
</P>
<P>
This African statesman, who presides over the Group of 77, also
traveled to Cuba's capital to preside over tasks at the first
summit conference that celebrated here countries on the way to
development making up this grouping.
</P>
<P>
The Nigeria leader will stay here Tuesday and Wednesday to hold
talks with President Castro and other high-ranking Cuban officials.
</P>
<P>
On Wednesday he'll preside over the inaugurating ceremony of
the South Summit, which will be attended by heads of state and
government as well as foreign ministers and other ministers from
the 133 member countries of the Group of 77. 
</P>
