<HEADLINE> EU to Speed Up Food Aid to Ethiopia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUXEMBOURG, April 10 (Xinhua) -- The European Union decided
Monday to speed up its food assistance toward Ethiopia as a follow-
up of its decision made at the Lisbon summit of EU heads of state
and government.
</P>
<P>
Christopher Patten, EU commissioner for external relations,
told the press that Monday's meeting of the general affairs
council of EU foreign ministers urged a speeding-up of EU
assistance.
</P>
<P>
The 15-nation bloc has pledged 50,000 tons of food aid to the
African country. So far 30,000 tons have been transported to their
destination.
</P>
<P>
The transport of another 16,000 tons of food will have to be
quickened to reach Ethiopia that has been baffled by famine.
</P>
<P>
Javier Solana, high representative of the EU common foreign and
defense policy, said that during the EU-Africa summit held last
week in Cairo of Egypt, the EU had talked with the leaders of both
Eritrea and Ethiopia about their border conflict.
</P>
<P>
The EU trio, that consisted of Patten, Solana and Portuguese
Foreign Minister Jaime Gama, briefed the general affairs council
of EU foreign ministers about their talks with the African leaders
on the regional conflict.
</P>
<P>
Later Monday, the EU foreign ministers are expected to meet
their Russian counterpart, Igor Ivanov, during the third EU-Russia
cooperation council.
</P>
<P>
Gama, whose country is holding the six-month rotating
presidency of the EU, said that Russia would talk with the
European Union about both issues of Chechnya and trade dispute.
</P>
<P>
The European Union would demand for free access to Chechnya for
international and humanitarian organizations to inspect the
violation of human rights in the region.
</P>
<P>
The EU and Russia are to discuss such trade disputes as the
Russian levy on scrap metal exports, regulation of the Russian
market for eggs, alcohol beverages and wine, intellectual rights
protection, financial services and overflight rights over Siberia.
</P>
<P>
The two sides will also review the progress made in the
implementation of the EU-Russia joint partnership and cooperation
agreement. 
</P>
</TEXT>
