<HEADLINE> Full Text of Agreement on Inter-Korean Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, April 10 (Xinhua) -- The following is the full text of
the agreement between South Korea and the Democratic People's
Republic of Korea (DPRK) on the summit between South Korean
President Kim Dae-jung and the DPRK leader Kim Jong-il in
Pyongyang on June 12-14.
</P>
<P>
"1. Reconfirming the three principles of national unification
declared by the Inter-Korean Basic Agreement on July 4, 1972,
South and North Korea agreed as follows in order to advance
national reconciliation, exchanges, cooperation, peace and
unification:
</P>
<P>
"2. President Kim Dae-jung will visit Pyongyang on June 12-14
at the invitation of National Defense Commission (NDC) Chairman
Kim Jong-il.
</P>
<P>
"3. During President Kim's trip in Pyongyang, there will be a
historic meeting between President Kim and NDC Chairman Kim, and
summit talks between them.
</P>
<P>
"4. Both parties agreed to hold preliminary contacts as early
as possible in April in order to discuss procedures related to
President Kim's visit to Pyongyang and the summit talks."
</P>
<P>
The agreement was concluded between Park Jie-won, South Korea's
culture and tourism minister, and Song Ho-gyong, vice chairman of
the DPRK's Asia-Pacific Peace Committee, in China last Saturday.
</P>
</TEXT>
