<HEADLINE> Diplomatic News Highlights (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
China expressed its welcome and support to the agreement
reached by the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) and
the Republic of Korea (ROK) that DPRK leader Kim Jong Il and ROK
president Kim Dae-jung will hold a summit meeting in Pyongyang in
mid-June.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman Zhu Bangzao said the Chinese
side hopes that the summit will yield positive results.
</P>
<P>
He said that it is China's consistent position to maintain and
promote peace and stability on the Korean Peninsula. The Chinese
side has all along stood for and supported the improvement of
relations and the realization of reconciliation between the North
and South of the Korean Peninsula through dialogue and
consultation, leading to the eventual realization of independent
and peaceful reunification.
</P>
<P>
China Demands Satisfactory Explanation on Bombing of Chinese
Embassy in Yugoslavia
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Government strongly demands that the U.S.
Government conduct a comprehensive and thorough investigation into
its bombing of the Chinese Embassy in Yugoslavia, bring the
perpetrators to justice and give the Chinese Government and people
a satisfactory explanation, Foreign Ministry spokesman Zhu Bangzao
said.
</P>
<P>
On April 8, the U.S. Government informed the Chinese
Government of the results of the accountability review concerning
the U.S. bombing of the Chinese Embassy in the Federal Republic of
Yugoslavia on May 8, last year, Zhu said.
</P>
<P>
The United States only admitted that the U.S. side used an
inappropriate methodology to locate the target and that the review
process at every level failed to find the mistake, he said.
</P>
<P>
According to the U.S. explanation, several individuals all
neglected their duties and its review process failed to detect the
mistake at every level, Zhu said. "This is hard for people to
believe."
</P>
<P>
China Independently Develops Satellite Perigee Solid Kick
Motor: Statement
</P>
<P>
China has developed the satellite perigee kick motor, known as
EPKM, entirely relying on its own efforts, according to a
spokesman of China Great Wall Industry Corporation.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman made the statement on the media reported charge
to Lockheed Martin by the U.S. State Department regarding the
alleged technical assistance of vehicle launching technology to
China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
