<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Party School Forms Academic Committee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 10 (Xinhua) -- An academic committee was set up
yesterday by the Party School of the Central Committee of the
Communist Party of China.
</P>
<P>
Hu Jintao, president of the school and vice-president of China,
attended the founding ceremony and issued certificates to the
appointed members of the committee.
</P>
<P>
As the Party School's highest honorary and consultative
academic organization, the committee includes prominent experts
and scholars of the school. The committee will discuss major
academic issues facing the country and offer suggestions for the
school's teaching and research programs.
</P>
<P>
"Facing the challenges of the new century, we are required to
further discuss and correctly answer the problems that occur in
China by using the theory of Marxism," Hu said.
</P>
<P>
He said the Party School is a field base for correct ideology
and theory as well as for cultivating the Party's cadres.
</P>
<P>
He expected the committee members to play a key role in
studying strategies for China's development. 
</P>
</TEXT>
