<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kunming Int'l Tourism Festival Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, April 10 (Xinhua) -- The China Kunming International
Tourism Festival opened today in the capital city of southwest
China's Yunnan Province, aiming to turn itself into a top tourism
magnet in China.
</P>
<P>
Zhu Shanzhong, an official with the National Tourism
Administration, said at today's opening ceremony that the efforts
made by Yunnan to develop tourism have set a good example for
China's other provinces.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that from 1995 to 1999, Yunnan registered sharp
growth in the number of overseas tourists and the revenue they
brought in, at an annual increase rate of 13.8 percent and 16.1
percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
Kunming successfully hosted the '99 World Horticultural
Exposition from May to October last year.
</P>
<P>
Shao Qiwei, deputy governor of Yunnan, said that the service
industry in Yunnan generated 63.12 billion yuan in added value
last year, accounting for 52 percent of the province's total gross
domestic product.
</P>
<P>
Tourism officials predict that the festival will attract about
five million tourists. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
