<DOCNO> XIE20000410.0062 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Anthropoid Statue Discovered in Northwestern Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 10 (Xinhua) -- An Iranian geographer recently
found a huge anthropoid statue made of stone in northwestern Iran,
similar to the statue of Sphinx, one of the seven wonders of the
world, the Islamic Republic News Agency reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The statue was found on a hill overlooking Anbaran village in
the city of Namin, some 40 kilometers away from Ardebil, the
capital city of the northwestern Ardebil province.
</P>
<P>
Residents of the village call the statue, 20 meters high and six
meters wide at the top of a 100-meter hill, as "Baba Davood"
(Father Davood) and believe that a shrine had been built in the
area surrounding the statue, but was destroyed with the lapse of
time.
</P>
<P>
Local residents have no exact information on why the statue is
called "Baba Davood" or about its historical beginning, the agency
said.
</P>
<P>
Projections resembling the eyes, mouth and chin of a person can
be seen on the face of the statue and it is believed that they have
been shaped by atmospheric changes, though a human role in the
shaping of the statue cannot be ignored. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
