<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 12 Militants, 3 Soldiers Killed in Kashmir </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Twelve militants and three
personnel of India's Border Security Force (BSF) were killed and
nine others wounded in intense gunfights between militants and
security forces in north Kashmir since Sunday evening, the Press
Trust of India (PTI) reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
Four "foreign mercenaries" were killed in a gun battle with
security forces at Nathpora village in Bandipora area of Baramulla
district, north Kashmir, Monday, the PTI quoted Senior
Superintendent of Police Qayoom Manhas in Baramulla as saying.
</P>
<P>
Also in Bandipora, another intense encounter between militants
and security forces broke out at Nasu village Sunday night, Manhas
said. Three militants associated with the Harkat-ul-Mujahideen
outfit and an equal number of BSF personnel were killed in the
battle while eight others, including five BSF soldiers, were
injured.
</P>
<P>
A big cache of arms and ammunition was recovered from the scene
of the encounter, the police officer added.
</P>
<P>
Police forces in Kashmir also gunned down five militants in an
exchange of fire at Pazalpora in the Rafiabad belt of Baramulla
Sunday evening, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
