<HEADLINE> King Sihanouk Meets French Senate Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Cambodian King Norodom
Sihanouk Monday met with visiting French Senate President
Christian Poncelet at the Royal Palace here.
</P>
<P>
Poncelet is at the head of a French Senate delegation, which
arrived here Monday for a two-day official visit at the invitation
of his Cambodian counterpart, Chea Sim.
</P>
<P>
King Sihanouk warmly welcomed Poncelet and his delegation and
thanked the French government and people for their great
contributions to Cambodia's cause of peace and reconstruction.
</P>
<P>
The king expressed his belief that Poncelet's visit will play a
positive role in strengthening the good cooperation between the
two countries, especially between the two senates.
</P>
<P>
Poncelet highly praised the realization of overall peace,
national reconciliation and unity in Cambodia and the progress
made by the royal government in other areas.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the 12-member delegation also met with Senate
President Chea Sim. The two sides exchanged views on some issues
of common concern.
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday, Poncelet will attend a ceremony for signing an
agreement on aid to be offered by the French government to
Cambodia.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time that the French Senate has sent a
delegation to Cambodia since the new Cambodian coalition
government was formed in November 1998. The delegation will leave
here Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
