<HEADLINE> Prisoners in Bangladesh Escape Amid Bombing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Fifteen prisoners under trial fled
Monday afternoon from a jail in Cox's Bazar, some 420 kilometers
southeast of here, after their associates exploded bombs and fired
gunshots at the police, the official Bangladesh News Agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
At least four policemen received gunshots and the conditions of
two of them are stated to be critical.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted Deputy Commissioner Pulin Behari Deb and
Superintendent of Police Lutfur Rahman of the port city as saying
an unaccounted number of terrorists attacked the jail. They threw
bombs and fired shots at the police on duty and broke open the
lock of the jail.
</P>
<P>
Eighteen under-trial prisoners out of a total of 64 confined in
the jail escaped, including five charged with murder.
</P>
<P>
The authorities are working to establish the identity of the
prisoners who escaped, the report said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
