<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Rejects West Pre-Conditions for Loans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian President Negaso
Gidada Monday criticized some Western countries for imposing
"unfair pre- conditions" on his country before they agree to offer
loans.
</P>
<P>
Addressing an opening ceremony of a political parties forum
here, Negaso said Ethiopia is making effort to build dams to make
extensive utilization of water resources.
</P>
<P>
"This endeavor requires a lot of fund...from international
financial institutions," however, he said, "the requirement of
unfair pre-conditions for acquiring the loans has made it
impossible for us to secure the loans."
</P>
<P>
Negaso urged the world community to put pressure on those
organizations that lay impossible pre-conditions on Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
He said that the government and people of Ethiopia has been
making serious efforts especially in the agricultural development
activities for achieving food self-sufficiency.
</P>
<P>
The president made the remarks when Ethiopia and other Horn of
Africa countries are facing famine crisis resulted from regional
drought.
</P>
<P>
More than eight million Ethiopians are suffering from
starvation, officials sources said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
