<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Makes Donation to OAU Peace Fund </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
by Zhao Yi
</P>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 10 (Xinhua) -- China presented to the Peace
Fund of the Organization of African Unity (OAU) a donation of
200,000 U.S. dollars which shall be used in the political
settlement of crisis in the Democratic Republic of the Congo
(DRC).
</P>
<P>
Chinese ambassador to Ethiopia Jiang Zhengyun and OAU Secretary
General Salim Ahmed Salim attended the presentation ceremony and
signed the documents on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said at the ceremony that China attaches great importance
to OAU's role in maintaining peace and stability in Africa.
</P>
<P>
The Lusaka Ceasefire Agreement, which was reached last year,
represents the achievement scored by African countries and OAU
with their own efforts in dealing with conflicts of the continent
through dialogue and consultation, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
"The donation reflects the goodwill and sincere friendship of
the Chinese people towards the African people," the Chinese
ambassador said, expressing the hope that the donation will
support the relentless efforts by African countries in seeking
solutions to African conflicts.
</P>
<P>
On behalf of his organization and African countries that are
involved in political settlement of the DRC crisis, Salim
expressed appreciation of China's donation towards African peace
process.
</P>
<P>
Salim also spoke highly of the positive roles that China has
played in the U.N. Security Council.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
