<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russian FM Stresses Importance of Russian-U.S. Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Russia regards the strengthening
of its relations with the United States and other Western
countries as a "priority of foreign policy," Russian Foreign
Minister Igor Ivanov said here Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Russian leadership "would like the relations between Moscow
and Washington to be a partnership" and the Russian-American
relations are entering "a new, very important phase," said Ivanov,
when meeting with a delegation of Western businessmen and
investors.
</P>
<P>
"Our approach to relations with the U.S. is not of a time-
serving character. We can positively cooperate in many spheres, "
he said.
</P>
<P>
They could include "strengthening international stability and
security, advancing disarmament progress, consolidating the non-
proliferation regime for mass destruction weapons and fighting
against international terrorism and organized crime," the minister
added.
</P>
<P>
Ivanov reminded that Russian President-elect Vladimir Putin had
reiterated Moscow's intention to "develop a constructive, mutually
advantageous dialogue with all countries, including both the U.S.
and member countries of the European Union."
</P>
<P>
The strategy of the new Russian leadership is absolutely
clearly directed at deepening economic reforms, creating a
favorable climate for foreign investors and expanding cooperation
with the West, Ivanov added.
</P>
