<HEADLINE> G-77 Opens Meeting, Adopts Agenda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, April 10 (Xinhua) -- The Group of 77 (G-77) developing
countries on Monday held an opening session of its South Summit in
Havana, capital of Cuba.
</P>
<P>
The opening session was presided over by Chairman of G-77
Arthur Mbanefo, who is from Nigeria, holder of the current
presidency of the group.
</P>
<P>
The session is designed to adopt the agenda of the South Summit,
the largest gathering of heads of state and government in the
organization's 36-year history.
</P>
<P>
The brief opening session will be immediately followed by a
closed-door meeting of senior officials from 133 G-77 member
states to hammer out the two final documents to be adopted at the
end of the summit on April 14.
</P>
<P>
The group is called G-77 because it was founded in 1964 with 77
members. 
