<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 30 MILF Rebels Killed in Southern Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Manila, April 10 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine government said
Monday that at least 30 Moro Islamic Liberation Front (MILF)
rebels and five soldiers were killed in fresh fighting in the
southern province of Lanao del Norte over the weekend.
</P>
<P>
According to armed forces spokesman Col. Rafael Romero,
government troops, backed by bomber planes and helicopters, were
poised to launch their final assault on Camp Bilal, the largest
MILF camp in Lanao del Norte.
</P>
<P>
Renewed fighting erupted between government forces and the MILF
in the towns of Balo-i and Munai last Friday when MILF guerrillas
tried to seize Balo-i, Romero said in a report.
</P>
<P>
"There is a continuous operation to clear up once and for all
the area of lawless elements and also to deny them (MILF) the base
from which they conduct their deprivation of civilians like
extortion and harassment," Romero said.
</P>
<P>
He said the fighting has displaced about 16,000 families but
they are being taken care of by government relief agencies.
</P>
<P>
The gunbattle now entering its fourth day on Monday has claimed
35 lives, including 30 MILF and five soldiers, Romero said, adding
that 18 government troops were wounded in the battle.
</P>
<P>
With the military offensive in full blast, Romero said Camp
Bilal is expected to fall in three days.
</P>
<P>
The military has deployed 2,400 troops to capture the MILF camp.
Two MILF strongholds, Camp Omar and Camp Jon Mac, were earlier
captured.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, MILF Military Chief Al Haj Murad said the MILF has
warned that it would back out of peace talks if government forces
continue to attack MILF-controlled territories in Lanao del Norte.
</P>
<P>
Murad expressed fears in a radio interview that the talks may
fail before the June deadline set out by Philippine President
Joseph Estrada.
</P>
<P>
The war that broke out in early March this year in Lanao del
Norte has left 200 MILF rebels and scores of government soldiers
dead.
</P>
<P>
The MILF has been fighting for an independent state in Mindanao
during the past two decades. 
</P>
</TEXT>
