<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing to Build Round-city Forest Belt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Beijing has begun to build a 100-
sq-km forest belt around the city.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Yunchang, spokesman for the Beijing Municipal
Afforestation Bureau, said today that the huge afforestation
project, which is to be completed by 2002, may be the biggest of
its kind in the history of afforestation in the world.
</P>
<P>
The forest belt, 40 percent of which has taken shape, is
located between the city's Second Ring Road and Fifth Ring Road.
</P>
<P>
The 100-sq-km forest will help protect Beijing residents from
dusty winds, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The pawpaw, bamboo, metasequoia and gingkgo and other tree
species are selected as the main trees for the belt, he added.
</P>
<P>
As part of the belt, nearly 100 cash orchards and gardens will
be built.
</P>
<P>
Beijing plans to increase its vegetation by 767 ha in its city
proper this year.
</P>
<P>
The central government departments have allocated a total of
about 120 million yuan (about 15 million U.S. dollars) to help
with Beijing's afforestation projects. 
</P>
</TEXT>
