<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Much of southern China is
expected to experience rainfalls ranging from three to 15 mm
during April 10-12, China's Central Meteorological Observatory
said today.
</P>
<P>
The observatory said part of the region will experience a
rainfall of up to 100 mm with occasional rainstorm or hailstorm
while a rainfall of two to five mm is forecast for the eastern
part of the Qinghai-Tibet Plateau.
</P>
<P>
Much of China to the south of the Yangtze River, Guizhou
Province and the Sichuan Basin reported rainfalls of three to 15
mm during the past three days until 5 a.m., Monday, with central
and southern parts reporting rainfalls ranging from 20 to 50 mm.
