<HEADLINE> Cold Air Current Advancing to Northern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Northern part of north China and
eastern part of northwest China are expected to experience a
moderate to strong northward breeze as a strong cold air current
is moving towards the regions during April 10 - 12, China's
Central Meteorological Observatory said here today.
</P>
<P>
Northern part of the Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region is
expected to have a snowfall of one to five mm during the three
days, and the northern part of north China, the central part of
Gansu Province, and the northern part of Qinghai Province will
have overcast weather from Tuesday night to Wednesday, the
observatory said.
</P>
<P>
The eastern part of northwest China is also expected to have a
snowfall of one to five mm with fresh to strong breeze for much of
northwest China and east China during Monday and Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
It said strong northward breeze to fresh gale is expected for
the Bohai Sea, the Yellow Sea and northern part of the East China
Sea with strong to whole gale for parts of the seas.
</P>
<P>
In addition, a strong breeze to moderate gale is forecast for
the central and south part of the East China Sea, the Taiwan
Strait and the northern part of the South China Sea.
</P>
<P>
Over the past weekend, much of northern China to the Yangtze
River experienced a cold air current moving southward with a drop
of up to 16 degrees centigrade in temperatures and dusty wind as a
result of the cold air current hitting part of south China and
northeast China.
</P>
<P>
The cold air current will disappear shortly as another one is
moving southward, the observatory said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
