<HEADLINE> Dogs to Patrol Chinese Borders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, April 10 (Xinhua) -- More than 200 police dog handlers
from over 10 provinces and regions of China gathered here today to
begin a six-month program on training for border patrol.
</P>
<P>
The officers are expected to bring a large number of police
dogs to be used for patrolling Chinese borders in the fight
against drug and weapons trafficking and other crimes, according
to the Helongjiang Frontiers Defense Bureau.
</P>
<P>
Stepped-up surveillance of border areas is believed to be the
most effective way to control China's drug-related crimes.
</P>
<P>
Formerly only a conduit for international drug-trafficking,
China has fallen victim to the narcotics trade, with more drugs
entering the country each year.
</P>
<P>
Police dogs have been playing an increasingly important role in
detecting drugs and traffickers. And the police trainees in the
new program are mainly from border provinces and regions,
including Guangxi and Yunnan, that are adjacent to the notorious "
Golden Triangle" in southeast Asia.
</P>
<P>
The Police Dog Training Base under the Helongjiang Frontier
Defense Bureau is the only police dog training center in China,
and has produced many highly-qualified dogs for police use across
the country.  
</P>
</TEXT>
