<TEXT>
<P>
ZHUIHAI, April 10 (Xinhua) -- The Gongbei Customs of Zhuhai
City, which controls the entries and exits from Macao, seized 81
smuggled cars worth 3.8 million yuan on April 5, a customs officer
said here today.
</P>
<P>
It is the biggest car smuggling case in the customs' history,
the officer said.
</P>
<P>
The illegal cargo included luxury cars such as BMW, Mercedes
Benz, Toyota, and automobile parts. The cargo left Hong Kong on
April 5 and was apprehended that night in the course of check-in
procedures.
</P>
<P>
The officer said that the customs has uncovered three car
smuggling cases so far this year, seizing 155 cars valued at 8.25
million yuan.  
