<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesian Attorney General Fails to Question Soeharto </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, April 10 (Xinhua) -- The Indonesian Attorney General's
Office on Monday failed again to question former President
Soeharto on corruption charges due to his bad health condition.
</P>
<P>
Soeharto still has a big trouble in his communication skills,
both spoken and written, an independent medical team set up by the
attorney general's office along with Soeharto's medical team said,
adding that the health condition of the former president is worse
than before.
</P>
<P>
"Before the team of prosecutors of the attorney general's
office launched investigation into Mr. Soeharto, we examined him,
particularly his cardiovascular, neurological and psychiatric
condition. And we concluded that the condition of Mr. Soeharto is
not good enough to face questioning. So we advised the prosecutors
not to launch investigation into him today," head of the
independent medical team, Supardi Sudibyo, told a press conference
at Soeharto's house.
</P>
<P>
"We are worried that if the prosecutors launch investigation,
Soeharto will experience a stroke again for the second time,"
Sudibyo added. He said Soeharto's blood pressure reached 180/90-95
mm/hg.
</P>
<P>
As many as eight prosecutors from the attorney general's office
previously were expected to further question the 79-year-old
former president to collect further information in connection with
his alleged involvement in corruption,collusion and nepotistic
practices during his 32 rule in the country.
</P>
<P>
The team arrived at Soeharto's residence in Central Jakarta at
about 01:00 p.m. (local time) Monday.
</P>
<P>
"After examining Soeharto, the independent medical team and
Soeharto's medical team said that Soeharto can not be questioned.
His blood pressure is still high. The medical team even said that
Soeharto's health condition is worse than before," Munthe, head of
the team, said at the press conference
</P>
<P>
But no details were provided on the health condition of the
former strong man who was forced to step down in May 1998.
</P>
<P>
Munthe also declined to answer questions about the policy the
attorney general's office will further take concerning the case.
</P>
<P>
"We don't know, whether or not it (investigation) will be
ceased or continued. We will report today's result to the attorney
general (Marzuki Darusman) and we will wait to see what kind of
step will be taken. Just wait," he added.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, Juan Felix Tampubolon, one of the Soeharto
lawyers, said his side is ready to cooperate with the attorney
general's office in connection with investigation into its client.
</P>
<P>
Early in April, prosecutors of the attorney general examined
Soeharto in connection with his alleged involvement in corruption,
collusion and nepotistic practices in social foundations he
chaired when he was still in office.
</P>
<P>
But the investigation was suspended due to the health condition
of Soeharto. 
</P>
</TEXT>
