<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia Welcomes DPRK-S.Korea Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Moscow said on Monday a summit
between the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) and South
Korea set for June will lead to "historic breakthroughs" on the
tension-filled Korean peninsula.
</P>
<P>
Confrontation and tension between the DPRK and South Korea "
could be sharply diminished" as a result of the coming
negotiations, said Director of the Russian Foreign Ministry's
First Asian Department, Leonid Moiseyev.
</P>
<P>
