<HEADLINE> China's Railway Earnings Top 20 Bn Yuan in 1st Qtr </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 10 (Xinhua) -- The Ministry of Railways said
today the sector earned 26.81 billion yuan in the first quarter
this year, up 8.1 percent from the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Of the total, income from train tickets during the three months
accounted for 9.98 billion yuan, increasing by 15.9 percent, and
that from cargo transport made up 13.08 billion yuan, up two
percent.
</P>
<P>
In the first quarter, China's railways carried 263 million
passengers, an increase of 6.9 percent on an annual basis. Cargo
transport volume stood at 393 million tons, up 2.9 percent, the
ministry said.  
</P>
