<HEADLINE> Kenyan University Launches Agro-Forestry Master's Degree Course </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Kenya's Kenyatta University has
launched a new master's degree program in agro-forestry and rural
development, the People daily reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
The 18-month program started in the 1999/2000 academic year
and has already enrolled five students, in collaboration with the
International Centre for Research in Agro-forestry (LERAF) based
in Nairobi.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Chancellor George Eshiwani of Kenyatta University said
that the course will benefit graduate students by providing them
the opportunities to conduct research.
</P>
<P>
The master's degree program aims at training and equipping
researchers and development workers with scientific tools to
enhance the understanding of agro-forestry and associated
technologies.
</P>
<P>
IERAF Director-General Pedro Sanchez said poverty, food
security and environmental degradation in sub-Saharan Africa
presented more challenges to his institution and collaborators
such as Kenyatta University. 
