<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Demands Satisfactory Explanation on Bombing of Chinese Embassy in Yugoslavia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 10 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Government strongly
demands that the U.S. Government conduct a comprehensive and
thorough investigation into its bombing of the Chinese Embassy in
Yugoslavia, bring the perpetrators to justice and give the Chinese
Government and people a satisfactory explanation, Foreign Ministry
spokesman Zhu Bangzao said here today.
</P>
<P>
On April 8, the U.S. Government informed the Chinese
Government of the results of the accountability review concerning
the U.S. bombing of the Chinese Embassy in the Federal Republic of
Yugoslavia on May 8, last year, Zhu said.
</P>
<P>
The United States only admitted that the U.S. side used an
inappropriate methodology to locate the target and that the review
process at every level failed to find the mistake, he said.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. side informed the Chinese side that it had sanctioned
eight CIA officers involved, with one of them fired, Zhu said.
</P>
<P>
"It must be pointed out that the Chinese Embassy in Yugoslavia
has unmistakable symbols and it is also clearly marked on the U.S.
maps. The U.S. claim that it did not know its exact location is
not justified," he said.
</P>
<P>
The Federal Directory of Supply and Procurement is not a secret
agency and its building is half a kilometer away from the Chinese
Embassy, Zhu said. The two buildings look totally different. "So
it was impossible for the U.S. side to mix up these two buildings,
" he said.
</P>
<P>
According to the U.S. explanation, several individuals all
neglected their duties and its review process failed to detect the
mistake at every level, Zhu said. "This is hard for people to
believe."
</P>
<P>
"The Chinese side once again stresses that the U.S. bombing of
the Chinese Embassy in the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia caused a
heavy casualty and severe damages to the embassy premises. In
committing this act, the U.S. side seriously violated the relevant
international conventions and basic norms governing international
relations, infringed gravely on China's sovereignty, greatly hurt
the dignity of the Chinese people and severely damaged Sino-U.S.
relations," he said. "This was an extremely serious international
unlawful act."
</P>
<P>
"The Chinese Government strongly demands that the U.S.
Government conduct a comprehensive and thorough investigation into
its bombing of the Chinese Embassy in Yugoslavia, bring the
perpetrators to justice and give the Chinese Government and people
a satisfactory explanation," the spokesman said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
