<HEADLINE> HK Stocks Finish Slightly Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks closed
slightly lower today for lack of fresh trading incentives.
</P>
<P>
The blue-chip Hang Seng index lost 90.94 points, or 0.54
percent, to close at 16,850.74.
</P>
<P>
Turnover was 9.33 billion HK dollars (1.196 billion U.S.
dollars), compared with Friday's 13.371 billion HK dollars (1.71
billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Of the four sub-indices of HSI, Finance, Utilities and Commerce
&AMP; Industry lost 0.90 percent, 0.17 percent and 0.98 percent,
respectively, while Properties gained 1.54 percent.
</P>
<P>
Hang Seng China Enterprises rose 0.40 percent, while Hang Seng
China-Affiliated Corporations Index went down 3.59 percent.
