<DOCNO> XIE20000410.0162 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iranian Reformers Seek Post of Majlis Speaker </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Iranian reformers are trying to
seize the post of Majlis (parliament) speaker after they won a
landslide victory over their conservative opponents in the sixth
parliamentary elections in February.
</P>
<P>
The May 23 Front, an alliance which groups 18 reformist parties,
is currently busy finalizing the list of its members of the
presiding board of the new parliament, including naming a candidate
for the post of speaker, the conservative daily Tehran Times
reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Quoting an informed source, the report said that Behzad Nabavi,
spokesman of the reformist alliance, is under mounting appeal to
accept the post of Majlis speaker.
</P>
<P>
Nabavi is a leader of the Islamic Revolutionary Mujaheddin
Organization, one of the major parties in the reformist May 23
Front, which was formed to mark the victory of reformist President
Mohammad Khatami in the 1997 presidential elections.
</P>
<P>
He served as government spokesman under former Prime Minister
Mir-Hossein Musavi in the 1980s and was minister of heavy industry
in former President Hashemi Rafsanjani's government.
</P>
<P>
If Nabavi took the post of speaker, he would be the first non-
cleric head of the parliament in Iran's post-revolution history.
</P>
<P>
According to an unnamed source, however, Nabavi insists that the
post of speaker should be filled by center-rightist Rafsanjani, who
entered the parliament but ranked the last in Tehran's list of 30
winners.
</P>
<P>
But Rafsanjani has declined to accept the post, as he prefers to
keep his post as chairman of the advisory and arbitrary State
Expediency Council, the source added.
</P>
<P>
Not all members of the May 23 Front agree with Nabavi's
speakership, the daily said, adding the Party of Constructive
Executives of Iran (PCEI), a centrist party which was inside the
front but close to Rafsanjani, is trying to find another candidate
for the post.
</P>
<P>
However, the paper did not disclose the name of the possible
candidate of the PCEI.
</P>
<P>
Another source told the paper that former mayor of Tehran
Gholamhussein Karbaschi, PCEI secretary general, recently met with
former Majlis Speaker Mehdi Karrubi and urged him to accept the
post of deputy speaker in the new parliament.
</P>
<P>
But Karrubi, secretary general of the Society of Combatant
Clergymen in Tehran, snubbed Karbaschi and turned down his
suggestion, the source said.
</P>
<P>
The May 23 Front, which bagged 189 seats out of 226 decided in
the first round of the February elections, has not announced its
candidate for the future Majlis speaker.
</P>
<P>
A run-off is to be held later this month to decide the winner of
the remaining 64 seats in the expanded 290-seat parliament.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000410.0163 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Arab League Urges Mine Clearance by Countries Responsible </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, April 10 (Xinhua) -- The Arab League has urged the
countries which sowed mines on Arab land to take responsibility for
the deadly legacy of past wars.
</P>
<P>
"The size of the problem in the Arab world is due to a lack of
maps and information about mine fields," the league's secretary-
general, Esmat Abdel-Meguid, said on Sunday in a speech read on his
behalf to an Arab regional symposium on land mines.
</P>
<P>
Two-fifths of the world's land mines were scattered on Arab
soil, Abdel-Meguid said.
</P>
<P>
He called for pressure on the countries that planted the mines,
as well as the United Nations and human rights organizations, to
solve the problem which has been impeding Arab development.
</P>
<P>
Hassan Issa, director of Egypt's National Center for Middle East
Studies, which organized the symposium, said Egypt alone has 19.7
million mines laid by Britain, Germany and Italy in the Western
Desert during the World War II.
</P>
<P>
Issa said 8,313 people were killed by mines spreading over 287,
000 hectares of Egyptian territory.
</P>
<P>
"The armed forces have only been able to remove 2.9 million
mines from 38,730 hectares of land," Issa said, adding that
clearing a single mine could cost 300 to 1,000 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Egypt has called on Britain, Germany and Italy to provide fund,
maps of mine fields and equipment for mine clearance. It sees the
aid offered by the three countries as meager.
</P>
<P>
Egypt also suffers from land mines and unexploded bombs left in
the Sinai Desert from its wars with Israel.
</P>
<P>
The final declaration of the first Africa-Europe summit held in
Cairo last week called for removal of existing mines, calling on
the states that had laid mines to provide money and know-how to
clear them and rehabilitate their victims.
</P>
<P>
A U.N. team visited Egypt in February to assess the land mine
problem, but has yet to release its findings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000410.0164 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam's Forest Coverage Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam's forest acreage in 1999
showed an increase of 1.5 million hectare (ha) compared with the
1995's figure, including 1.2 million ha of natural forests,
Vietnam News Agency reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam had a total of 10.9 million ha of forests by the end of
1999, hence a forest coverage of 33.3 percent, according to the
country's Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Development (MARD).
</P>
<P>
The MARD's estimates were made on the basis of the reports by
46 of the country's 58 provinces having forests.
</P>
<P>
Of the total, as many as 9.5 million ha are natural forests,
while 1.4 million ha are planted ones, not counting the areas
grown with scattered trees and industrial trees.
</P>
<P>
The four Central Highlands provinces of the country topped the
list with 2.99 million ha of forests, followed by the northeastern
provinces with 2.33 million ha.
</P>
<P>
The regions which recorded high increases in afforestation in
the past five years included the northeastern region (up 689,240
ha), the northwestern region (up 403,429 ha), the mid-central
region (up 257,937 ha), and the northern central region (up 161,
850 ha).
</P>
<P>
Vietnam is carrying out a program to plant five million ha of
forests by the year 2010, raising forest coverage to 43 percent.
The country plans to grow 200,000 ha of concentrated forests this
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
