<P>
ZAGREB -- The Croatian government Sunday okayed an
investigation by international war crimes tribunal experts into an
alleged mass grave site suspected of containing the bodies of
ethnic Serbs killed by Croatian troops during the 1991-1995
Bosnian war.
</P>
<P>
A statement from the government's information office said that
the decision was made on the basis of international commitments
Croatia shoulders, related laws on cooperation with the
International War Crimes Tribunal in The Hague, the Netherlands,
and other important norms, local media reported. (Croatia-
Tribunal-Probe)
