Shevardnadze won over 82 percent, leaving far behind ex-Communist
leader Dzhumber Patiashvili who bagged only 17 percent of the vote,
Itar-Tass news agency reported, citing an official with the
Georgian Central Election Commission. (Georgia-President Election-
Shevardnadze) 
