<DOCNO> XIE20000410.0190 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> French Academy Regrets Degrading of Education of Literature </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 10 (Xinhua) -- The French Academy on Monday
expressed its deep regret over the degradation of the teaching of
French literature in public schools over the past two decades.
</P>
<P>
The members of the Academy said that over the past two decades,
the classes on literature in French schools have been reduced "to
the point of almost completely eliminating our teaching of the
knowledge and taste of literature."
</P>
<P>
They blamed the government of abolishing the teaching of the
ancient languages like Latin and Greek in public schools, which
they said are essential for understanding the French.
</P>
<P>
"Today, the language and literature themselves seem to have
become the enemies who destroy our culture," they said.
</P>
<P>
The Academicians also said that the principle of equality in
education can no longer help strengthen the teaching of literature
in France, because the overall teaching standard is falling.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000410.0191 </DOCNO>
