<HEADLINE> Poll Shows Most Swedish People Against Joining Euro Zone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Most of the Swedish voters are
opposed to joining the European Economic and Monetary Union (EEMU),
according to the result of a survey published by Dangens Industri
newspaper on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Among those polled, 40 percent were against the entry, with 36
percent for and 24 percent undecided, said the country's biggest
economic daily.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, two other major newspapers in the country published
similar results of their own polls on the issue.
</P>
<P>
Sweden's ruling Social Democratic Party passed a bill on March
10 to support the country to join the EEMU. 
</P>
