<HEADLINE> New Zealand Olympic Shooting Team Formed  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, April 10 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand shooting team
for the Sydney Olympic Games has been formed.
</P>
<P>
The New Zealand Press Association (NZPA) reported Monday that
the team is composed of Brant Woodward (trap), Victor Shaw (trap),
Desmond Coe (double trap), Brian Thomson (skeet), Geoffrey Jukes (
skeet), Teresa Borrell (trap), and Tania Corrigan (air pistol, 25m
pistol).
</P>
<P>
Only trap shooter Brant Woodward has previous experience of an
Olympic Games. He appeared at the Atlanta Olympics four years ago.
</P>
<P>
All other six New Zealand shooters will make their Olympic
Games debuts at Sydney in September.
</P>
<P>
Tania Corrigan, who won two silver medals and one bronze medal
at the 1998 Commonwealth Games, is the only shooter selected for
competing in two events. She will compete in the air pistol and
the 25m pistol, formerly known as sport pistol.
</P>
<P>
Brant Woodward, Desmond Coe, Brian Thomson, Geoffrey Jukes and
Tania Corrigan were all members of New Zealand's team at the 1998
Commonwealth Games in Kuala Lumpur. 
</P>
