Morocco, in the last two World Cup finals, beat Gambia 1-0 away
via a solitary strike by Bouchaib Lembarki.
</P>
<P>
It was their first game under new coach Henryk Kasperczak, the
former Polish international.
</P>
<P>
Tunisia triumphed 2-1 in Mauritania and South Africa edged
neighbours Lesotho 2-0 in Maseru with goals from new captain Shaun
Bartlett and debutant Jabu Pule. 
