<HEADLINE> Commonwealth Champion out of Olympic Women's Marathon  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Heather Turland, Australia's
1998 Commonwealth Games women's marathon champion, ruled herself
out of contention for the Sydney Olympic Games on Monday,
According to reports from Sydney.
</P>
<P>
The 40-year-old mother of four, choking back tears at a press
conference in Sydney, explained that a six week break from
training because of a viral infection had thwarted her qualifying
bid for the Sydney Olympics.
</P>
<P>
Turland, who has not run a qualifying time for the Olympic
marathon, had planned to run in Rotterdam next Sunday to achieve
the two hour 33 minute mark.
</P>
<P>
Turland, who overcame a broken leg in her buildup to the Kuala
Lumpur Commonwealth Games, said she might yet defend her title in
Manchester, England, in 2002. 
</P>
</TEXT>
