<DOCNO> XIE20000410.0202 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Interest Tax Growth Reported In East China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, April 10 (Xinhua) -- East China's Jiangsu Province,
one of China's leading economic giants, collected 96 million yuan
(11.6 million US dollars) in interest taxes in March, a big leap
from 41 million yuan in February and 17 million yuan in January.
</P>
<P>
The growth in interest taxes is due to local people's
preference for saving money in banks rather than to invest and
spend. The introduction of interest tax is aimed to increase the
locals' initiatives to spending instead of saving their money.
</P>
<P>
By the end of February, savings and deposits in Jiangsu
Province had topped 441 billion yuan (53.1 billion US dollars), a
10.7 percent rise on a yearly basis.  
</P>
</TEXT>
