<BODY>
<HEADLINE> "Pollen Rain" Falls in Central China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, April 10 (Xinhua) -- "Pollen rain" fell in Changsha
in central China's Hunan Province last week, which experts said
was not harmful to human health.
</P>
<P>
People suspected that the yellow-colored downpour brought on
April 5 was industrial pollution or waste gas. Many parents did
not allow their children to go outdoors for fear of being infected.
</P>
<P>
After tests were conducted, the municipal environment bureau
said that the yellow-colored downpour was large amounts of rape
pollen.
</P>
<P>
The vegetable is the most popular plant in central China's
Hubei and Hunan provinces. It is presently the flower season for
rape.  
</P>
</TEXT>
