<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Muscle Cells A Possible Substitute For Marrow </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, April 10 (Xinhua) -- A group of muscle cells has been
discovered as possible substitutes for bone marrow to effectively
treat AIDs and leukemia.
</P>
<P>
Pang Wenxin, an assistant researcher with the China Concord
Medical University, discovered the group of muscle cells.
</P>
<P>
Muscle cell treatment could be more helpful in curing leukemia
at a much less cost.
</P>
<P>
Malignant tumors and immunology deficiency diseases such as
AIDs, kill more than 10 million people around the world each year.
</P>
<P>
The hemopoietic stem cell transplant is believed to be the most
efficient way curing these diseases to date. 
</P>
</TEXT>
