<HEADLINE> China Supports Upcoming DPRK-ROK Summit (More Added) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 10 (Xinhua) -- China today expressed its welcome
and support to the agreement reached by the Democratic People's
Republic of Korea (DPRK) and the Republic of Korea (ROK) that DPRK
leader Kim Jong Il and ROK president Kim Dae-jung will hold a
summit meeting in Pyongyang in mid-June.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman Zhu Bangzao said this here
today. The Chinese side hopes that the summit will yield positive
results, he added.
</P>
<P>
Today, Zhu said, The DPRK and ROK announced that the two sides
had reached agreement on holding the North-South Summit, and that
DPRK leader Kim Jong Il and ROK president Kim Dae-jung will hold a
summit meeting between the North and South of the Korean peninsula
in mid-June in Pyongyang.
</P>
<P>
He said that it is China's consistent position to maintain and
promote peace and stability on the Korean Peninsula. The Chinese
side has all along stood for and supported the improvement of
relations and the realization of reconciliation between the North
and South of the Korean peninsula through dialogue and
consultation, leading to the eventual realization of independent
and peaceful reunification.
</P>
<P>
"The Chinese side welcomes and supports the agreement reached
by DPRK and ROK on the first ever summit meeting between top
leaders of the two sides since the division of the Korean
Peninsula. It is our sincere wish that the meeting will yield
positive results," Zhu said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
