<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Compiles Biography for Outstanding Scientists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 10 (Xinhua) -- A series of biographies of
thousands of noted Chinese scientists is being compiled by the
China Association for Science and Technology (CAST).
</P>
<P>
The books aims to spread scientific spirit among ordinary
Chinese through the outstanding achievements of Chinese scientists.
</P>
<P>
More than 1,320 scientists who have made great contributions to
China from 1840 to 1920 have been included in the 29-volume book.
</P>
<P>
More than 330 experts took part in the editing the book and a
large amount of material about pioneers of Chinese modern science
have been included.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Yutai, CAST vice-president, said that the second stage of
the series, expected to be completed by 2015, will include all the
well-known Chinese scientists born before 1945. Editorial work has
begun for the third stage of the project concentrating on modern
Chinese scientists. 
</P>
</TEXT>
