<HEADLINE> China Speeds up Development of GIS Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 10 (Xinhua) -- A senior official with the
Ministry of Science and Technology said China is pushing ahead
development of geological information system (GIS) software
industry which plays an important role in China's economy and
security.
</P>
<P>
Li Jian, head of high and new technology department of the
Ministry of Science and Technology made the remarks here at the
ongoing conference on application of China-made GIS software.
</P>
<P>
He said China will have the China-made GIS software occupy 40
to 50 percent of the domestic market by the end of this year,
adding that the development of the GIS industry is also of great
importance in building a digital China and the knowledge-based
economy.
</P>
<P>
China will build several demonstration bases of the GIS
industry in next five years and push ahead computerized upgrading
of five to 10 industries.
</P>
<P>
The development and industrialization of the GIS software has
been listed as one of a major national scientific and
technological research programs between 1996 to 2000.
</P>
<P>
GIS software is widely used in resource surveys, environment
evolution, regional development planning, administration of public
installations, communications, telecommunications, energy and
other fields.
</P>
<P>
The three-day conference on the application of China-made GIS
software will end tomorrow. 
</P>
</TEXT>
