<HEADLINE> International Business Forum Held in Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, April 10 (Xinhua) -- A Macao-Beijing international
business forum opened here Monday morning in order to strengthen
the economic and trade cooperation among enterprises in Portuguese-
speaking areas, and China's inland areas and the Macao Special
Administrative Region (SAR).
</P>
<P>
About 500 representatives of the business sector from Africa,
Europe and China's inland areas and Macao are participating in the
forum.
</P>
<P>
During the three-day conference, they will discuss Macao's role
as a bridge for the development of small and medium-sized
enterprises around the world, trading opportunities in the world's
Portuguese-speaking areas, and the impact of information
technology on business in the new century.
</P>
<P>
Delivering a speech at the opening ceremony of the forum,
Francis Tam Pak Un, secretary for economy and finance of the Macao
SAR government, said that the founding of the SAR marked a new era
for Macao, and that the Macao SAR government will continue to
enhance economic and trade ties with other areas of the world.
</P>
<P>
"The conference has brought together business partners from
different corners of the world, and it will in turn offer varied
cooperation channels and unlimited business potentials," the
official said.
</P>
<P>
Organized by the Portuguese Speaking Entrepreneurs Association,
the forum will end in Macao on April 12 and reopen in Beijing on
April 14. 
