<HEADLINE> Bus Accident Kills 6, Injures 43 in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Six people were killed on the
spot and 43 others injured when a bus in which they were
travelling ran off the road in the central hill country in Sri
Lanka, press reports said Monday.
</P>
<P>
The bus was plying from Badulla to Thennapanguwa in central Sri
Lanka when it toppled over a 56 meter precipice on Saturday
evening at Dunhinda, some 230 km east of Colombo, the private
newspaper Island said.
</P>
<P>
Among the dead was the driver of the bus, the report said.
</P>
<P>
However, it did not indicate the cause of the incident.
</P>
<P>
With the assistance of local residents the police were able to
extricate the dead and the injured who were rammed inside the bus,
said the report, adding that the injured were transported to the
Badulla base hospital for treatment.
</P>
<P>
The police was carrying out further investigations. 
</P>
