<HEADLINE> Western Region of Nepal Faces Food Shortage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, April 10 (Xinhua) -- The mid-western parts of Nepal
are facing severe food supply shortages due to lack of traffic
facilities, according to reports reaching here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Reports from different districts of Karnali Zone of mid-western
Nepal said food stock has reached the bottom level and people are
already facing food shortages.
</P>
<P>
Even in some better districts, grain stock can only last up to
the end of this month, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
"The government needs to do something fast. We have asked them
for help and have been assured of help within a week," said Mohan
Baniya, who is leading a delegation to the capital seeking for
help.
</P>
<P>
Karnali Zone is the nation's only zone without any road network
and depends on the government to fly in food supplies and
distribute it at subsidized rate. The remote and inaccessible
villages of this part of the country suffer from food shortages
every year. 
</P>
