<HEADLINE> Ukraine Begins First Arctic Expedition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, April 9 (Xinhua) -- The first Ukrainian arctic expedition
team composed of its own experts started off Sunday toward the
North Pole, local media said.
</P>
<P>
"Today is a historic day. The Ukrainian national flag will fly
over the North Pole, and all the Ukrainians will watch closely the
whole process of the expedition," said Defense Minister Alexander
Kuzmuk, who saw an advance team off at Borispole airport.
</P>
