<HEADLINE> Fairly Strong Quake Hits Eastern Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, April 10 (Xinhua) -- A fairly strong earthquake
measuring 4.9 on the open-ended Richter scale jolted eastern Japan
Monday morning, the Meteorological Agency said.
</P>
<P>
There were no immediate reports of casualties or damage, and no
tsunami or tidal wave warning was issued.
</P>
<P>
The quake, which occurred at 6:30 a.m. local time (21:30 GMT,
Sunday), hit a wide area in the region including Ibaraki, Tochigi,
Gunma, Saitama, Chiba, Kanagawa prefectures and Tokyo, the agency
said.
</P>
<P>
The epicenter of the quake was estimated at 60 kilometers
underground in the southern part of Ibaraki Prefecture, the agency
said. 
</P>
