<HEADLINE> Georgia's Shevardnadze Re-Elected President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Georgian President Eduard
Shevardnadze has secured a second five-year term in Sunday's
presidential elections, according to preliminary results.
</P>
<P>
With 81 percent of the vote counted early Monday morning,
Shevardnadze won over 82 percent, leaving far behind ex-Communist
leader Dzhumber Patiashvili who bagged only 17 percent of the vote,
Itar-Tass news agency reported, citing an official with the
Georgian Central Election Commission.
</P>
<P>
Four other candidates won virtually no support.
</P>
<P>
Initial statistics show that about 67 percent of the country's
3,028,000 registered voters cast their ballots.
</P>
<P>
Tass quoted sources as saying that Shevardnadze will be
inaugurated on April 30. 
