<HEADLINE> United States Romps into Davis Cup Semis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 9 (Xinhua) -- Andre Agassi and Pete Sampras
snatched the last two singles, sending the United States to the
Davis Cup tennis semifinals.
</P>
<P>
Agassi beat Jiri Novak of the Czech Republic 6-3, 6-3, 6-1 to
tie the quarter-final 2-2 in Inglewood, California. Sampras
followed with 18 aces in a 6-4, 6-4,7-6 (2) win over Slava Dosedel
in the final match to clinch a 3-2 victory.
</P>
<P>
The United States will play Spain, a 4-1 winner over Russia,
beginning July 21 in Spain.
</P>
<P>
Playing a fifth and decisive match for the first time in his
seven-year Davis Cup career, Sampras hit a backhand winner off a
182-kph serve by Dosedel to win the tiebreaker 7-2 and set off a
celebration among the 12,000 fans at the Forum.
</P>
<P>
In other Davis Cup matches, Brazil joined defending champion
Australia in the semifinals. Australia defeated Germany 3-2 and
will next face Brazil, a 3-2 winner over Slovakia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
