<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Magic Edges Philadelphia 76ers 92-80 in NBA Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 9 (Xinhua) -- Orlando continued its push for
a playoff berth by beating Philadelphia 76ers 92-80 in Orlando on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Ron Mercer led five players in double figures with 17 points as
the Magic moved two games ahead of Milwaukee in the race for the
eighth playoff spot in the Eastern Conference. Orlando, which has
won eight of nine, visits the Bucks on Monday night.
</P>
<P>
Orlando hounded Philadelphia into a season-low 32.9 percent (26-
of-79) on field goals attempts.
</P>
<P>
In Charlotte, North Carolina, Eddie Jones, Derrick Coleman and
Elden Campbell each scored 19 points as Charlotte clinched a
playoff berth after defeating Indiana Pacers 96-80.
</P>
<P>
Campbell added 13 rebounds, and Anthony Mason had 18 points and
10 rebounds.
</P>
<P>
In Houston, Rockets outclassed Utah Jazz 99-90. Steve Francis
scored a game-high 26 points.
</P>
<P>
It was the third straight win for the Rockets and sixth in
their last eight games.
</P>
<P>
Walt Williams scored 21 points while Cuttino Mobley had 16 and
former Jazz sixth man Shandon Anderson 13.
</P>
<P>
John Stockton led Utah with 23 points. Karl Malone had 20 and
Bryon Russell 16 as the Jazz saw a three-game win streak end.
</P>
<P>
In Miami, Heat had a 95-94 overtime victory over the New York
Knicks. Tim Hardaway's desperation 3-pointer as time expired in
overtime allowed Miami to close in on its fourth straight Atlantic
Division crown.
</P>
<P>
The Knicks led most of the game, but now the Heat own a three-
game edge over New York in the standings with six remaining. Miami
also has the tiebreaker edge, having taken the season series from
New York for the first time, 3-1.
</P>
<P>
Miami is also just one game behind Eastern Conference leader
Indiana, which lost Sunday to Charlotte 96-80.
</P>
<P>
In Sacramento, California, Phoenix Suns defeated Sacramento 102-
97. Penny Hardaway had 25 points, 12 rebounds and six assists as
Phoenix completed a four-game season sweep of Sacramento.
</P>
<P>
Jason Williams had 24 points for the Kings, who have lost three
of four.
</P>
<P>
In Vancouver, British Columbia, San Antonio Spurs overwhelmed
Grizzlies 107-99. Tim Duncan had 31 points and 11 rebounds, and
Terry Porter added a season-high 22 points, as San Antonio stayed
a half-game behind fourth-place Phoenix in the Western Conference
standings.
</P>
<P>
Mike Bibby scored 24 points, Shareef Abdur-Rahim had 23 points
and 11 rebounds, and Michael Dickerson scored 20 for Vancouver.
</P>
<P>
In Oakland, California, Golden State Warriors knocked out
Denver Nuggets 117-103. Larry Hughes had a career-high 44 points.
Adonal Foyle added a career-high 18 points and 13 rebounds and
Mark Davis had 17 points for the Warriors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
