<HEADLINE> Poland's Swimmer Disqualified over Residency Requirements </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Poland's Kasia Kulesza was
disqualified from an Olympic synchronized swimming test event
Monday after the world's governing body FINA ruled she did not
meet residency requirements, according to reports from Sydney.
</P>
<P>
Under FINA regulations, any competitor changing her affiliation
from one national governing body to another must have resided in
their new country for at least 12 months before an event.
</P>
<P>
FINA said Kulesza competed for Canada in a World Cup tournament
in Seoul in September 1999.
</P>
<P>
Reserve Olga Niewitecka took her place next to Anna Antoniewska
in the duet technical competition on Monday. Poland finished 29th
in the field of 34 duet teams. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
