<HEADLINE> Facts &AMP; Figures: Major Export Commodities to Netherlands in Jan., Feb. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 10 (Xinhua)-- Following are the latest
statistics of China's major export items to the Netherlands in the
first two months of 2000, provided by the General Administration
of Customs:
</P>
<P>
Export of machines, electronic goods, audiovisual equipment and
relevant parts and accessories was 400.589 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Export of metals and related products was 116.056 million U.S.
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Export of chemical material and products was 74.457 million U.S.
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Export of textile materials and products was 54.931 million U.S.
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Export of plastics and products was 43.194 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Export of optical, medical machinery, clocks and watches and
musical instruments was 31.524 million U.S. dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
