<HEADLINE> Facts &AMP; Figures: Trade with Top Ten Partners in 1st Two Months (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BEIJING, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Following are the facts and
figures of China's trade with its top ten partners in the first
two months of 2000, provided by the General Administration of
Customs:
</P>
<P>
-- Two-way trade with Japan, 10.675 billion U.S. dollars, up
41.6 percent. Exports to Japan, 5.106 billion U.S. dollars, up 35.
3 percent; imports 5.569 billion U.S. dollars, up 48 percent.
</P>
<P>
-- Two-way trade with the European Union, 9.417 billion U.S.
dollars, up 46.1 percent. Exports to EU, 5.295 billion dollars, up
41.7 percent; imports, 4.122 billion U.S. dollars, up 52.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
-- Two-way trade with the U.S., 9.375 billion U.S. dollars, up
31.9 percent. Exports to the U.S., 6.474 billion US dollars, up 33.
6 percent; imports, 2.901 billion US dollars, up 28.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
-- Two-way trade with Hong Kong, 6.787 billion U.S. dollars,
up 47.7 percent. Exports to Hong Kong, 5.686 billion U.S. dollars,
up 51.7 percent; imports from Hong Kong, 1.101 billion U.S.
dollars, up 29.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
-- Two-way trade with ASEAN countries, 4.533 billion U.S.
dollars, up 37.6 percent. Exports to ASEAN, 1.906 billion U.S.
dollars, up 33.4 percent. Imports, 2.627 billion U.S. dollars, up
40.8 percent.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
