<HEADLINE> Facts &AMP; Figures: Trade with Top Ten Partners in 1st Two Months (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
-- Trade volume with the Republic of Korea, 4.406 billion U.S.
dollars, up 51.7 percent. Exports to ROK, 1.427 billion U.S.
dollars, up 54.1 percent; imports, 2.979 billion U.S. dollars, up
50.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
-- The mainland's trade volume with Taiwan, 3.719 billion U.S.
dollars, up 33.0 percent. Exports to Taiwan, 646.271 million U.S.
dollars, up 35.7 percent; imports, 3.073 billion U.S. dollars, up
34.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
-- Trade volume with Australia, 1.293 billion U.S. dollars, up
74.3 percent. Exports to Australia, 465.726 million U.S. dollars,
up 37.6 percent; imports 827.739 million U.S. dollars, up 103.2
percent.
</P>
<P>
-- Total volume with Canada, 1.046 billion U.S. dollars, up 83.
5 percent. Exports, 426.844 million, up 37.1 percent. Imports, 619.
009 million U.S. dollars, up 139.2 percent.
</P>
