<HEADLINE> Facts &AMP; Figures: Trade with 6 Continents in 1st Two Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 10 (Xinhua)-- Following are the latest facts and
figures about China's foreign trade with countries and regions in
Asia, Africa and Latin America in January and February 2000,
provided by the General Administration of Customs:
</P>
<P>
-- Asia-oriented trade volume, 33.951 billion U.S. dollars,
up 46.8 percent; Exports, 16.361 billion U.S. dollars, up 42.8
percent; imports, 17.590 billion U.S. dollars, up 50.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
-- Africa-bound trade volume, 1.294 billion U.S. dollars, up
86.3 percent. Exports, 649.697 million U.S. dollars, up 33.8
percent; imports, 644.005 million U.S. dollars, up 208.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
-- Latin America-related trade volume, 1.459 billion U.S.
dollars, up 70.7 percent. Exports, 892.958 million U.S. dollars,
57.6 percent; imports, 565.924 million U.S. dollars, up 96.3
percent.
</P>
<P>
-- North-America-bound trade reached 10.421 billion U.S.
dollars, up 35.6 percent. China's Exports, 6.901 billion U.S.
dollars, up 33.7 percent; imports, 3.520 billion U.S. dollars, up
39.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
-- China's trade with Europe, 11.675 billion U.S. dollars, up
51.0 percent. China's exports to Europe, 6.231 billion U.S.
dollars, up 45 percent; imports 5.444 billion U.S. dollars, up 58.
5 percent.
</P>
<P>
-- China's Trade with Oceania, 1.460 billion U.S. dollars, up
69.3 percent. China's exports, 537.476 million U.S. dollars, up 38.
1 percent; imports, 922.594 million U.S. dollars, up 95.1 percent.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
