<HEADLINE> Facts &AMP; Figures: Foreign Trade of China's Special Economic Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 10 (Xinhua) -- The following are the latest
facts and figures about the foreign trade of China's special
economic areas in the first two months of this year, released by
the General Administration of Customs.
</P>
<P>
Trade turnover of China's Special Economic Zones (SEZ), 7.204
billion U.S. dollars, up 46.2 percent. Exports of the SEZs, 3.719
billion U.S. dollars, up 50.0 percent; and imports, 3.485 billion
U.S. dollars, up 42.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
Trade turnover of Economic and Technological Development Zones
and Special Open Areas, 5.631 billion U.S. dollars, up 65.4
percent. Exports, 2.370 billion U.S. dollars, up 50.3 percent;
imports, 3.261 billion U.S. dollars, up 78.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
Trade turnover of Hi-Tech Industrial Development Zones, 1.718
billion U.S. dollars, up 47.3 percent. Exports, 717.548 million U.
S. dollars, up 29.7 percent, and imports, 1.001 billion U.S.
dollars, up 63.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
Trade turnover of China's Bonded Areas, 1.876 billion U.S.
dollars, up 92.1 percent. Exports, 646.351 million U.S. dollars,
up 32.8 percent; and imports, 1.230 billion U.S. dollars, up 150.9
percent.
</P>
<P>
Trade turnover of China's 14 coastal open cities, 17.491
billion U.S. dollars, up 50.8 percent. Exports, 9.154 billion U.S.
dollars, up 35.4 percent; and imports, 8.337 billion U.S. dollars,
up 72.4 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
