<HEADLINE> Facts &AMP; Figures: Trade of China's 5 Special Economic Zones </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BEIJING, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Following are facts and figures
about the foreign trade in China's five special economic zones (
SEZ) in the first two months of 2000, provided by the General
Administration of Customs:
</P>
<P>
The Xiamen SEZ -- total foreign trade turnover, 982.170
million U.S. dollars, up 37.7 percent. Exports, 583.460 million U.
S. dollars, up 52.7 percent; imports, 398.710 million U.S. dollars,
up 20.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
The Shenzhen SEZ -- total foreign trade turnover, 4.390
billion U.S. dollars, up 42.7 percent. Exports, 2.124 billion U.S.
dollars, up 30.5 percent; and imports, 2.266 billion U.S. dollars,
up 56.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
The Zhuhai SEZ -- total foreign trade turnover, 907.514
million U.S. dollars, up 44.0 percent. Exports, 362.472 million U.
S. dollars, up 31.7 percent; and imports, 545.042 million U.S.
dollars, up 53.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
The Shantou SEZ -- total foreign trade turnover, 741.074
million U.S. dollars, up 112.0 percent. Exports, 544.243 million U.
S. dollars, up 335.7 percent; and imports, 196.831 million U.S.
dollars, down 12.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
The Hainan SEZ -- total foreign trade volume, 183.185 million
U.S. dollars, up 16.2 percent. Exports, 105.159 million U.S.
dollars, up 49.1 percent; and imports, 78.027 million U.S. dollars,
down 10.5 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
