<HEADLINE> Facts &AMP; Figures: China's Trade by Month in 2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BEIJING, April 10 (Xinhua)-- Following are the latest
statistics of China's foreign trade from January to February 2000,
provided by the General Administration of Customs:
</P>
<P>
-- Total volume of foreign trade in January topped 32.056
billion U.S. dollars, up 50.8 percent from the same period of 1999.
Exports in the month grew 47.8 percent to 16.797 billion U.S.
dollars, and imports rose 54.2 percent to 15.259 billion U.S.
dollars.
</P>
<P>
-- February saw total foreign trade increase of 43.2 percent
from the same month of 1999, to 28.204 billion U.S. dollars, with
exports standing at 14.775 billion dollars, up 34.5 percent, and
imports 13.429 billion dollars, up 54.1 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
