<HEADLINE> Facts &AMP; Figures: Trade of Enterprises With Overseas Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BEIJING, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Following are facts and figures
about trade volumes of enterprises with overseas capital in China
in the first two months of 2000, provided by the General
Administration of Customs:
</P>
<P>
-- The total trade volume of enterprises with overseas capital,
29.174 billion U.S. dollars, up 45.6 percent. Exports, 14.305
billion U.S. dollars, up 37.2 percent; and imports, 14.869 billion
U.S. dollars, up 54.8 percent.
</P>
<P>
-- The total trade volume of Chinese-foreign contractual joint
ventures, 2.402 billion U.S. dollars, up 41.8 percent. Exports, 1.
280 billion U. S. dollars, up 40.5 percent; and imports, 1.122
billion U.S. dollars, up 43.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
-- The total trade volume of Chinese-foreign equity joint
ventures, 13.057 billion U.S. dollars, up 43.1 percent. Exports,
6.033 billion U.S. dollars, up 34.9 percent; and imports, 7.024
billion U.S. dollars, up 51.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
-- The total trade volume of solely foreign-funded enterprises,
13.764 billion U.S. dollars, up 48.8 percent. Exports, 6.991
billion U.S. dollars, up 38.6 percent; and imports, 6.773 billion
U.S. dollars, up 61.2 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
