<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Highlights of Major Beijing-based Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Highlights of today's major
Beijing-based newspapers:
</P>
<P>
"People's Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- A news story reports how Shandong Province's Binzhou
prefectural committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC)
strengthens ideological work to help people become rich in coping
with the new circumstances.
</P>
<P>
-- The Fourth China East-West Cooperation and Investment Trade
Fair ended up yesterday in Xi'an, capital of Shaanxi Province,
with a volume of transaction worth over 100 billion yuan (12
billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
 "Xinhua Daily Telegraph"
</P>
<P>
-- A national conference was held in Kunming of southwestern
China's Yunnan Province from April 6 to 8 to find ways to stop
malfeasance in certain government departments and some trades.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji said in a letter to the meeting that
in response to public outcry against misconduct by government
officials and professionals, more must be done to improve
education and supervision of the individuals and groups involved.
</P>
<P>
-- Multinational big companies have started cooperating with
China's west regions in a bid to share the vast market there.
</P>
<P>
 "China Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- Developing China's west requires the efficient use of
resources and the application of science, said Tian Fengshan,
China's new Minister of Land and Resources.
</P>
<P>
-- Top Chinese officials over the weekend denounced Taiwan's "
vice-president-elect" Annette Lu as detrimental to cross-straits
relations, for making what they call separatist remarks.
</P>
</TEXT>
