<HEADLINE> China To Host Int'l Forum on Ecology, Environmental Protection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QINGDAO, April 10 (Xinhua) -- China will host an international
forum on ecology and environmental protection in the port city of
Qingdao, in east China's Shandong province, on April 27-28.
</P>
<P>
The forum is being organized according to the proposals of
environmental protection officials, financial experts and
entrepreneurs from developed countries.
</P>
<P>
High-ranking officials from Germany, Luxembourg, the United
States, Britain, Brazil, China and international organizations, as
well as world-famous environmental experts and representatives of
environmental protection enterprises are expected to attend the
forum and will focus on discussing how to effect a harmonious
development of economy, society and the environmental protection
industry.
</P>
<P>
They will also talk about issues such as information and
resource sharing in the field of ecological environment and
related industries, rational development and use of resources and
ecological environmental protection, and cooperation between
enterprises. 
</P>
</TEXT>
