<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Court Cases Related to Relocation Project in Three Gorges Dam Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Two courts in Chongqing
Municipality in southwest China have handled over 1,600 cases
related to the massive resettlement of residents affected by the
Three Gorges dam project since construction of the project started
in 1993.
</P>
<P>
An official in charge of the municipality's No. 2 Intermediate
People's Court said that cases related to the relocation project
were up 70 percent a year.
</P>
<P>
Since 1995, 106 people on charges of misappropriating and
embezzling government funds allocated for resettling affected
people in the massive Three Gorges project have been brought
before the courts.
</P>
<P>
Wang Sumei, a cashier of the Wanzhou Resettlement Bureau, was
sentenced to death on charges of spending 1.26 million yuan of
government funds on gambling.
</P>
<P>
Some 473 million yuan of funds earmarked for the Three Gorges
Resettlement Project have been misappropriated in the past few
years.
</P>
<P>
Official figures show that the central government allocated
over 17.6 billion yuan for resettlement purpose in the Three
Gorges Project by 1999.
</P>
<P>
The relocation project will involve 1.13 million people in 20
counties and prefectures by 2009 when the Three Gorges Project is
completed.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
