<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Liverpool Move to Second in Premier League Placing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 9 (Xinhua) -- Liverpool moved above Leeds United
into second place in the English premier league on Sunday after
goals from Czech Patrik Berger and Michael Owen clinched a 2-0
victory over Tottenham Hotspur.
</P>
<P>
Leeds lost 1-0 at Aston Villa, their third successive league
defeat. Liverpool have 62 points from 32 games, eight points
behind leaders Manchester United who play at Middlesbrough on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
Leeds, who have had a traumatic week after two of their fans
were killed in Turkey before a UEFA Cup semifinal against
Galatasaray, have 60 points with six games left.
</P>
<P>
Czech international Berger ran across the edge of the penalty
area and struck the ball home superbly in the 34th minute. England
striker Owen slotted home a pass from new striking partner Emile
Heskey in the 61st minute to seal the win at Anfield.
</P>
<P>
Leeds title hopes were destroyed by a controversial Julian
Joachim goal in the 39th minute.
</P>
<P>
Leeds felt Joachim had pushed Gary Kelly off the ball before
bursting away on his own to score.
</P>
<P>
A minute's silence was held before the kickoff for the two dead
Leeds supporters. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
