<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2200 GMT, Sunday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Iran on Sunday unilaterally released 500 Iraqi
prisoners of war (POWs) left over from the 1980-88 bloody war
between the two neighbors.
</P>
<P>
The Iraqi POWs were set free through the Khosravi border point
in Iran's Kermanshah province at a ceremony attended by officials
from the two countries and representative of the International
Committee of the Red Cross, the Islamic Republic News Agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
It is the first stage of Iran's unilateral release of 2,000
Iraqi POWs to be followed by other stages, Kameran Bakhtiari, an
Iranian official at the border point, was quoted as saying. (Iran-
Iraq-POWs)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BAGHDAD -- Saadoun Hamadi was reelected the speaker of the new
Iraqi National Assembly (parliament) during a meeting on Sunday,
reported the Iraqi News Agency (INA).
</P>
<P>
This is the second time in succession for Hamadi to hold the
post, which will last four years.
</P>
<P>
Hamadi was elected speaker of the parliament in the last
parliamentary elections in March 1996. Since then, he has been
holding the post, one of the most important positions in Iraq.
(Iraq-Parliament)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak said Sunday that
he is not optimistic about chances of reviving the Israeli-Syrian
peace talks, Israel Radio reported.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the weekly cabinet meeting Sunday morning, Barak
confirmed he will discuss with U.S. President Bill Clinton during
their Washington summit on Tuesday about new peace ideas from
Syrian President Hafez al-Assad.
</P>
<P>
However, he added, the summit will focus mainly on the Israeli-
Palestinian final-status talks and the planned Israeli troops
withdrawal from south Lebanon. (Israel-Syria-Talks)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BEIRUT -- Hezbollah guerrillas on Sunday claimed responsibility
for a Katyusha rocket attack on northern Israel following an
earlier Israeli shelling which injured four Lebanese.
</P>
<P>
Israeli army has confirmed the rocket attack, but there were no
immediate reports of casualties.
</P>
<P>
Hezbollah said in a statement that it had fired on "Israeli
positions on the border," including crossing points into northern
Israel. (Lebanon-Israel-Rocket Attack)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Iran said on Sunday that it has stopped a Panamanian
oil tanker suspected of carrying smuggled Iraqi oil in the Persian
Gulf.
</P>
<P>
The official IRNA news agency quoted the elite Islamic
Revolutionary Guards Corps (IRGC) as saying the seizure was made
after the tanker, "Ramim al-Khaleej," violated Iranian territorial
waters.
</P>
<P>
IRNA said the tanker gave no heed to the warnings and the IRGC
patrol fired blank shots and forced it to stop. The tanker asked to
be allowed to return to Iraq where it had loaded the oil, which was
apparently refused, and it is now under control of the IRGC navy.
(Iran-Tanker-Interception) 
</P>
</TEXT>
