<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2100 GMT, Monday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Iran on Sunday night released another batch of 500
Iraqi prisoners of war (POWs) left over from the 1980-88 bloody war
between the two neighbors, the Islamic Republic News Agency
reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Governor of Qasr-e Shirin of the western Kermanshah province
Asfandiar Zakeri said that the group of Iraqi POWs left Iran
through the Khosravi border point in the province at a ceremony
attended by officials from the two countries and representative of
the International Committee of the Red Cross.
</P>
<P>
It was the second group of Iran's unilateral release of 2,000
Iraqi POWs, and the first group of 500 Iraqi POWs left Iran on
Sunday morning. The other 1,000 POWs are scheduled to be released
in the coming days. (Iran-Iraq-POWs)
</P>
