BAGHDAD -- The headquarters of the Iranian opposition group
Mujahidin Khalq in southern Iraq were shelled Sunday by mercenaries
infiltrating into Iraq from "a neighboring country," announced an
Iraqi official on Monday.
</P>
<P>
