- - - -
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- An Iranian geographer recently found a huge anthropoid
statue made of stone in northwestern Iran, similar to the statue of
Sphinx, one of the seven wonders of the world, the Islamic Republic
News Agency reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The statue was found on a hill overlooking Anbaran village in
the city of Namin, some 40 kilometers away from Ardebil, the
capital city of the northwestern Ardebil province.
</P>
<P>
Residents of the village call the statue, 20 meters high and six
meters wide at the top of a 100-meter hill, as "Baba Davood"
(Father Davood) and believe that a shrine had been built in the
area surrounding the statue, but was destroyed with the lapse of
time.(Iran-Statue)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak is heading to
Washington Monday afternoon on a mission to inject more vitality
into the faltering Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
Barak is due to meet U.S. President Bill Clinton in Washington
on Tuesday to try to rescue the stalled peace talks with the
Syrians and push ahead the final-status talks with the
Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
He will also discuss with Clinton about Israel's planned troop
withdrawal from south Lebanon by July this year.(Barak-Clinton-
Summit)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
