<DOCNO> XIE20000410.0327 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ecuador's Volcano Erupts Again </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
According to IGEPON, the "mountain of fire", about 10
kilometers west from the capital city of Quito, registered Sunday
18 emissions of vapor and ash, as well as over one hundred quakes.
</P>
<P>
During the emissions, one could see columns of steam and ash
reaching a height of about 800 meters with rosy grey color, while
a sulphur odor was very strong.
</P>
<P>
IGEPN reported a descent in the number of quakes continues, but
the number of emissions of steam with low amount of ash have
risen in recent days.
</P>
<P>
Future emissions which could be even larger than those
registered in recent days aren't left out, said IGEPN in a
communique recommending keeping conditioned yellow alert in Quito
and in towns near the volcano.
</P>
<P>
Volcano Guagua Pichincha, or baby Pichincha, 4,794 meters high
above sea level, has been relatively stable since December last
year, following its biggest ever eruption registered November 25,
1999, during which at least 500,000 tons of volcanic ash fell upon
Quito city. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000410.0328 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Halts Flights of Osprey Aircraft after Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Osprey crashed during a night training mission at Marana
Northwest Regional Airport in Arizona State on April 8, killing
all 19 aboard.
</P>
<P>
Marine Corps spokesman Lamdon Hutchens said that all"operations
and evaluations flights" would be stopped while investigators
looked into the cause of the crash.
</P>
<P>
The investigators spent Sunday reviewing the crash site, but
released few details. There was no immediate indication what
caused the crash.
</P>
<P>
The Osprey, which can take off like a helicopter and fly like a
plane,is part of a new generation of aircraft scheduled to replace
all of the Marines' primary troop-transport helicopters.
</P>
<P>
The aircraft, jointly produced by Bell Helicopter Textron Inc.
and Boeing Co., has been under development for more than a decade.
</P>
<P>
The plane was introduced last September and the Marines have
ordered 360 Ospreys to be delivered by 2014 at a cost of 44
million U.S. dollars each.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
