<HEADLINE> UN Peacekeepers Attacked in Sierra Leone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
On Saturday night, unknown attackers fired at the headquarters
of the Ghanaian troops based at Kenema in eastern Sierra Leone. U.
N. troops fired back at the attackers, but there were no
casualties reported on either side, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. Mission in Sierra Leone (UNAMSIL) is investigating the
incident, believed to be the first of its kind.
</P>
<P>
UNAMSIL was established in October 1999 to assist the
Government and the parties in carrying out the Lome peace
agreement aimed at ending hostilities between the rebels and the
Government and forming a government of national unity.
</P>
<P>
According to Security Council Resolution 1289 adopted on 7
February 2000, the UNAMSIL was expanded to a maximum of 11,100
military personnel. 
</P>
