<HEADLINE> Group - 77 Backs Reducing North-South Technological Gap </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
G-77 held here a closed-door meeting of senior officials from
its 133 member states at the end of a brief opening session of
the South Summit.
</P>
<P>
"The process of quick accumulation of knowledge and
technologies hasn't gotten to hundreds of millions of persons that
keep on living in absolute poverty", said the group in its draft
Joint Declaration published Monday.
</P>
<P>
Southern Summit of the Group of 77 will take place from April
12 to 14 in Havana with the participation of heads of State or
government of member countries.
</P>
<P>
Group-77 said it commits itself to the promoting of scientific
and technological development with an increase in resources, the
developing of an adequate institutional framework, including the
achieving of quality and advanced education.
</P>
<P>
"We're exhorting developed countries to facilitate a
technological transfer easing costs and colateral conditions
hindering it", the document said.
