<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, April 10 (Xinhua) -- The National Resistance Movement
(NRM), the ruling party of Uganda, has launched its national
referendum campaign here Monday, which will decide the political
future of the party as well as that of the east African country.
</P>
<P>
Ugandan President Yoweri Museveni who declared the party's
decision at the International Conference Center said at a press
conference that it is a crucial move of the party toward the June
referendum.
</P>
<P>
Museveni, also NRM chairman, said that the country under the
leadership of NRM has achieved success in politics, economy,
education, and other fields, and it is NRM that brings people of
different shades of opinions to work together under one unified
political roof.
</P>
<P>
In Ugandan history, the country had suffered from failure of
multi-party system, because it was based on political
sectarianism, said the president, adding that the NRM guarantees
democracy because it represents interests of all groups.
</P>
<P>
He appealed to the electorate to participate actively in the
coming referendum and urged them to vote for his party.
</P>
<P>
Under the 1995 Constitution, a national referendum is to be
held in June 2000 to decide on the country's political system. It
is widely believed that the NRM would come out a winner. 
