<HEADLINE> U.N. Peacekeepers Under Attack in S. Leone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, April 10 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations' peacekeeping
forces in Sierra Leone Saturday night came under attack in
Kenerma, the eastern town of the war-torn west African country,
said a source reaching here Monday.
</P>
<P>
A U.N. spokesman was quoted as saying that a group of unknown
assailants attacked the U.N. military base in Kenema near the
Liberian border.
</P>
<P>
The two sides exchanged gunfire for more than an hour, yet no
causalities were caused during the shoot-out.
</P>
<P>
According to the spokesman, this exchange of gunfire was one of
the most serious incidents to take place since the United Nations
began its peacekeeping operations in Sierra Leone earlier this
year to enforce a peace agreement between the government and rebel
forces.
</P>
<P>
About 7,000 peacekeepers are currently deployed in the west
African country. 
</P>
