<HEADLINE> Angela Merkel Elected New Chairman of German CDU </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BERLIN, April 10 (Xinhua) - Germany's opposition party, the
Christian Democratic Union (CDU) had elected 45-year-old Angela
Merkel as its new chairman on Monday at its party convention in
Essen.
</P>
<P>
Angela Merkel came from former eastern Germany and is the
incumbent secretary general of the CDU. She was elected to the
important position of the big German conservative party with a
thumping majority. It expressed great hopes that she would pull
the party out of its disastrous finance scandal since last
November.
</P>
<P>
Merkel had won an absolutely 96 per cent of the vote with 897
delegates casting ballots for her, 38 against and seven abstaining.
</P>
<P>
The convention had elected Ruprecht Polenz as new secretary
general of the party and four deputy party chairmen at the same
time.
</P>
<P>
Merkel said before beginning of the party convention: "There
is a chance in every crisis - we will seize this chance."
</P>
<P>
But can Merkel extricate the CDU from the present difficult
situation? Nobody can answer this question now. 
</P>
</TEXT>
