<DOCNO> XIE20000410.0352 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Roundup: German CDU Elects Merkel New Chairman  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
ESSEN, Germany, April 10 (Xinhua)--Germany's opposite
Christian Democrats (CDU) Monday formally elected Angela Merkel
the first female chairman at their 13th national congress here.
</P>
<P>
Merkel, 45 and a former physics teacher from a east German
pastor's family, won some 96 percent supporting vote among 1,001
delegates from all over Germany.
</P>
<P>
Most have predicted Merkel's election, but her voting result
is by far the best one in CDU's history.
</P>
<P>
Merkel's predecessor Wolfgang Schaeuble won 93 percent at the
congress in the year of 1998, and Helmut Kohl won 87 percent when
he first elected CDU chairman in 1973.
</P>
<P>
Schaeuble, the ill-fated "crown prince" of Kohl, was forced to
step down amid a funding scandal of himself. But he still held a
seat in the new CDU presidium.
</P>
<P>
Also elected to the CDU leading circle was Ruprecht Polenz, a
53-year old legislator from Muenster city who will manage the
party as general secretary. The new face emerging into the CDU
presidium won some 88 percent of vote.
</P>
<P>
In her speech to the congress, Merkel urged the CDU to unite
around her and win the general election in the year 2002.
</P>
<P>
"The time of our enemy has gone away, we are here again, to
the business," she said.
</P>
<P>
The CDU, haunted by former chancellor Helmut Kohl's illicit
funding scandal, should forget Kohl, look forward, and turn the
crisis into chance, Merkel told the party.
</P>
<P>
She vowed to begin structural and financial reforms, enhance
the internal democracy, and turn the west-rooted conservative CDU
into a real "people's party".
</P>
<P>
In the hour-long speech, Merkel also hit Chancellor Gerhard
Schroeder's red-green coalition cabinet, contending Schroeder's "
new middle" policy.
</P>
<P>
Merkel said: "every policy of Schroeder is a lie-- the
ecological tax, social welfare and tax reform, eastern
construction!--there are lie no.1 through no.5. "
</P>
<P>
The CDU delegates welcomed her speech with long-time hails and
applauded for six minutes.
</P>
<P>
Merkel, unknown to the public just half a year before, is seen
as an outsider who will lead the party in another style. The CDU's
grass-rooted members call Merkel her nick name "Angie" and try to
find another Magarette Thatcher in her.
</P>
<P>
To re-build the party finance, which is near bankrupt after
the government pursued huge fines against the CDU for Kohl's
scandal, Merkel and other CDU leaders also planned to raise
monthly party membership fee by one mark each.
</P>
<P>
Kohl, the former CDU chairman whose reputation was ruined
after acknowledging to have collected undeclared campaign funds,
did not take part in the congress, though he said in an open
letter to Merkel and Schaeuble that "the CDU remains my political
homeland." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000410.0353 </DOCNO>
