<HEADLINE> Production of Industrialized Countries Threatens the Planet:G-77 . </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
HAVANA, April 10 (Xinhua)-- The Southern Summit of the Group of
77 said Monday that the production systems of industrialized
countries are unsustainable and threaten the planet's survival.
</P>
<P>
This summit, that takes place from Wednesday to Friday in
Havana, demanded in its draft Joint Declaration that before its
application, technological innovations are submitted to economic,
social and environmental evaluation.
</P>
<P>
The block proposed that in this project participate
governments, entrepreneurial and scientific communities and other
groups that have been excluded from this kind of decisions.
</P>
<P>
G-77 exhorted industrialized nations to submit to developing
countries environmentally safe technologies.  
