<HEADLINE> CA Announces Jasmine Iapplication Suite for B2B, B2C Selling and Procurement  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW ORLEANS(USA), April 10 (Xinhua) -- Computer Associates
International, Inc.(CA) on Monday announced a suite of Jasmine
powered applications that can dramatically improve the ability of
companies to win on the Web by accelerating Commerce solution
deployment.
</P>
<P>
The announcement was made here at CA-World 2000, the largest
educational conference and exposition for enterprise computing
professionals, to be held from April 9-14 in New Orleans,Louisiana,
the United States.
</P>
<P>
The Jasmine iapplication Suite delivers complete out-of-the-
box functionality for fast and cost-efficient Business-to-
Business(B2B0 and Buiness-to-Consumer (B2C) selling and
procurement.
</P>
<P>
It builds on the power of Jasmine and CA's patented Neugents
technology to develop customized personalized exchanges and
portals that meet the needs of increasingly demanding customers,
thereby promoting customer retention and securing repeat business.
</P>
<P>
"The Jasmine iApplication Suite delivers tremendous speed and
quality advantages in the race to eBusiness," said Charles B. Wang,
Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of CA.
</P>
<P>
 "It is ideally suited for dot.coms and born-on-the-Web
startups as well as established brick-and-mortar companies
committed to a rigorous transition to the click-and-mortar-
business model," he said.
</P>
<P>
 Built from the ground up to ensure complete manageability
through CA's award-winning Unicerter TNG enterprise management
solution, the Jasmine iApplication Suite provides integrated and
secure B2B and B2C eBusiness. It includes:
</P>
<P>
 -- Jasmine iMarket, which provides complete catalog
merchandising facilities coupled with a dynamically personalized
customer portal powered by Neugent. It delivers completed orders
to internal sales order processing systems or to affiliated
eBusiness partners over the Internet.
</P>
<P>
 -- Jasmine iProcure, which provides complete management of
buyers and approval processes. Vendor product catalogs are
directly integrated to produce a purchasing portal. Jasmine
iProcure sends purchase orders to internal purchasing systems or
directly to vendors over the Internet.
</P>
<P>
-- Jasmine iService, which enable partners and clients to
extend the Jasmine iApplication Suite.
</P>
<P>
CA, the world's leading business software company, delivers
the end-to-end infrastructure to enable eBusiness through
innovative technology, services and education.
</P>
<P>
 CA has 18,000 employees worldwide and has revenue of 6.3
billion U.S. dollars for the year ended December 31, 1999.
</P>
</TEXT>
