<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CA Ships Suite of Jasmine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW ORLEANS (USA), April 10 (Xinhua) -- Computer Associates
International Inc.(CA) on Monday began full-scale delivery of the
Suite of Jasmine,the world's first intelligent and integrated
platform for eBusiness.
</P>
<P>
Leveraging CA's patented Neugents neutral-network technology,
Jasmine is the only solution to enable unique and dynamically
personalized Internet Exchanges and portals for Business-to-
Business (B2B) and Business-to-Consumer(B2C) commerce.
</P>
<P>
"Today's eBusiness world requires incredible speed -- speed of
delivery, speed of decision making, and speed of bringing diverse
buyers and sellers together," said Charles B. Wang, Chairman and
Chief Executive Officer of CA.
</P>
<P>
"You have to do it fast, and you have to do it right. Jasmine
provides everything you need to intelligently embraces eBusiness
with unprecedented scale and speed," he said.
</P>
<P>
Formally launched today at CA-World 2000, the largest
educational conference and exposition for enterprises computing
professionals to be held from April 9-14 in New Orleans, Louisiana,
the United States, Jasmine has been in testing at more than 2,000
client and partner sites since last July.
</P>
<P>
CA, the world's leading business software company, delivers
the end-to-end infrastructure to enable eBusiness through
innovative technology, services and education.
</P>
<P>
CA has 18,000 employees worldwide and has revenue of 6.3
billion U.S. dollars for the year ended December 31, 1999.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
