<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Simitis Receives Mandate to Form New Government </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
ATHENS, April 10 (Xinhua) -- Greece's ruling Panhellenic
Socialist Movement (PASOK) leader and Prime Minister Costas
Simitis Monday received a mandate from President Costis
Stephanopoulos to form a new government following the ruling party
's victory in the country's parliamentary elections Sunday.
</P>
<P>
After calling on Stephanopoulos to receive the mandate,
Simitis said that he would seek to form a government in the next
few days having renewal and continuity as priorities, while the
priority issues in the next four-year term would be the social
state and employment.
</P>
<P>
With the new government, Simitis stated, a new circle of
reforms would be launched that would open new horizons and would
make Greece stronger and more present than before.
</P>
<P>
Greek business leaders Monday also urged Simitis' new
government to move ahead briskly with planned structural changes
to the country's economy.
</P>
<P>
Reliable sources said that the new government would be formed
by Wednesday or Thursday, while the new parliament would convene
for the first time on April 20 and the new parliament presidium
would be elected on April 21. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
